track_notes: The crux of this climb is between the summit ridge and the access to the first Twin.  My route would probably get the Canadian scrambling grade SC-7.  SC-5 is Easy, SC-6 is Moderate and SC-7 is difficult.  If you go to climbers left of my track to follow a drainage gully up, you can probably keep on SC-6 terrain.  Although my route is technically SC-7,  it is on good solid, secure rock so it gives a greater sense of security.
